\SE[9] Now, let's confirm the strategy once again! \SE[50] Soon,
we will begin clashing with the main force...

\SE[53]Reluctantly, it seems that they have the upper hand in
terms of military strength. The support of the Magic Academy is
an insurmountable advantage! \SE[54]So, what should we do?...
Well then, Vega, give me your answer!

\SE[20]I will divide the troops into two. The main force will
attract the enemy's attention... \SE[19]while a small
infiltration unit will take down their main stronghold.

\SE[16]Yes, that's good! \.It's regrettable, but my main force in
the front will be a decoy! \!\SE[52]We'll pretend to fight and
then withdraw the troops at the right moment!

\SE[16]Well...! If it seems like we can actually win, let's go
for the victory...!!

\SE[9]Now, what kind of infiltration route should we use?
\SE[50]Laura, why don't you give it a try and answer!!

\SE[99]There is a cave beneath the river that separates the
border. \.We can infiltrate the underground sewer of Cordain from
there.... \!\SE[100]After that, we can join forces with Princess
Ulysseene's reinforcements....

Yes, there's no problem! If I may add, the proposal for the
infiltration route was suggested by Cat-san!

\SE[16]Hmm, you remembered well! Impressive! \SE[52]Indeed, you
are a true citizen of Ulysseene!!

Excuse me!! \.I can see Cordain's main force on the opposite
bank! \!It seems they are already in a state of readiness for
battle!
